item.title: A Dream
item.description: Lionel Johnson, July 1883 Did I ever tell you a strange kind of dream I had a few months ago ? I was sleeping quietly when I felt a shock go right through me, and I seemed to have left my body behind, and gone off to the stars ; I saw myriads of lights streaming over and on a vast white lake : I was in a state of perfect ecstasy, when I felt myself whirled back to my body, and woke up with a violent sense of splitting headache.

item.title: Abc
item.description: This is just a test. Last week I got a really bad migraine that knocked me out for 2 days. I ordered groceries –which is something I really never do– and requested 2 cans of ready-to-bake biscuit dough. I hadn’t eaten in days and went through the canned biscuits fast… I ate a whole can in one day. I regret it a little bit. ⊕ dummy!!! you big dummy!!!
